space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The problem requires finding the minimum number of changes needed to make substrings of length k semi-palindromes. We iterate through the string s from the beginning to the end (O(n)) and for each substring of length k, check if all characters are the same. If they are, increment the changes count. If not, the changes count is incremented. The minimum number of changes is stored in the result variable, and the count of changes is stored in the count variable. Finally, the function returns the result plus the count.

The time complexity is O(n) because we iterate through the string once. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a single integer variable for result and count. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs a constant number of operations per iteration, and the number of iterations is proportional to the length of the string.

